# Architecture

Flow: `src/app` route → thin component → `src/modules/*/service.ts` → contracts/types → `src/app/api` → `src/lib/persistence`

# Non-negotiable rules

- Keep modules independent
- No business logic only in page components
- Use API layer between UI and services
- Do not mix exam logic with progress logic
- Do not mix saved progress with content logic
- Keep Read Aloud separate from revision and quiz logic
- Keep Access Arrangements independent from other modules
- All student progress must auto-save where applicable
- Mobile-first UI and accessibility-first design
- Follow connected learning architecture: `docs/design/09_SENECA_ARCHITECTURE_COMPARISON/ARCHITECTURE-PRINCIPLES.md` (documentation only — one primary CTA per route, Power Grid centrality, Saved Progress glue, Recommendations as brain)

# Build priority order

1. Exam Engine
2. Power Grid
3. Saved Progress
4. Read Aloud
5. Dashboard
6. Timed Assessments
7. Full GCSE Exams
8. Content Fact-Checking And Editorial Workflow
9. Results
10. Recommendations
11. Accessibility
12. Access Arrangements foundation

Do not skip higher-priority work unless explicitly overridden. Record the reason in `HANDOFF.md`.
